                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91293/187: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-16T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 16, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 16—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>581. Legation’s 484, June 23, 4 p.m. Marshal Yen<note n="81" xml:id="d633fn81"
                        >Yen Hsi-shan, of Shansi, leader of the rebellion against the Chinese
                        Government at Nanking.</note> has issued an order restoring Hallett Abend’s
                    press privileges. Abend intends to come to Peiping within a few weeks.<note
                        n="82" xml:id="d633fn82">The Minister in China on October 27, 1930,
                        reported, in telegram No. 936, from Peiping, that Hallett Abend had informed
                        him of the satisfactory adjustment of his status vis-à-vis the Nanking
                        Government—arranged apparently by the Chinese Minister of Finance, T. V.
                        Soong (893.00/11271). Press privileges were not fully restored, however,
                        until April 28, 1931 (811.91293/195).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
